html:
378 U.S. 127

84 S.Ct. 1658

12 L.Ed.2d 744

Barbara ELFBRANDT
v.
Imogene R. RUSSELL et al.

No. 553, Misc.

Supreme Court of the United States

June 15, 1964

W. Edward Morgan, for petitioner.

Robert W. Pickrell, Atty. Gen. of Arizona, Philip M. Haggerty, Asst. Atty. Gen., and Norman E. Green, for respondents.

On Petition for Writ of Certiorari to the Supreme Court of Arizona.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for a writ of certiorari are granted. The judgment is vacated and the case is remanded to the Supreme Court of Arizona for further consideration in light of Baggett v. Bullitt, 377 U.S. 360, 84 S.Ct. 1316.
